&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Infinite Medical P.C.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Infinite Medical P.C. is a nationwide network of advanced practice providers and specialty clinicians committed to delivering high-quality, proactive care directly to residents in skilled nursing and long-term care facilities. Our partnership with MedElite Healthcare Management Group empowers us to focus on what matters most: providing compassionate, personalized care that meets the unique needs of each resident. Together, we champion continuous innovation and collaboration in our shared mission to redefine senior care across the country.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Infinite Medical P.C. is seeking an Attending Physician to take on the responsibility of overseeing and managing the primary medical care for residents at our facilities. In this role, you will act as the primary care provider for the patients, ensuring their overall health and well-being. You will have a dedicated full-time Nurse Practitioner (NP) or Physician Assistant (PA) to support you in this role, working collaboratively with you to provide excellent patient care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position offers a unique opportunity for professional growth, with the potential to evolve into a Medical Director/Attending Physician leadership role for candidates interested in expanding their clinical and administrative responsibilities within the organization.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the primary care provider for residents in Skilled Nursing Facilities (SNFs), taking responsibility for their medical management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct patient rounds, collaborating with NPs and PAs to assess and manage resident care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Diagnose and treat patients with acute illnesses while overseeing the management of ongoing medical conditions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Discuss treatment plans, prognosis, and advance care planning with residents and their families&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate medical records and ensure adherence to healthcare regulations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with nurses, therapists, and specialists to provide comprehensive care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A board-certified physician with experience in primary care and long-term care (LTC).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong leadership skills and the ability to effectively support and mentor NPs and PAs in delivering care.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be able to lift a minimum of 20 pounds and stand / walk / work on your feet up to 6-8 hours per day&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Total Annual Compensation:&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;$100,000 - $120,000&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paid Time Off&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sign-on Bonus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Malpractice Insurance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
